{
  "texts": [
    "TTUR uses stochastic gradient learning g(, w) of the discriminator's loss and h(, w) of the generator's loss.",
    "It defines the true gradients of g(, w) = ∇ w L D and h(, w) = ∇ L G with random variables M (w) and M as shown in Eq. 21 reported from Heusel et al. (2017).",
    "So, it uses stochastic learning b(n) and a(n) for updating the discriminator and generator steps respectively as defined in Eq. 22 reported from Heusel et al. (2017).",
    "However, the choice of appropriate learning rates depends on the GAN architecture, type of experiments, and nature of the datasets.",
    "Abdelhalim et al. (2021) investigated the use of both TTUR (Heusel et al. 2017) and discriminator updates in SPGGAN for skin lesion image synthesis."
  ]
}